ut 1162","1138":"1138","1214":"1214","1245":"1245","1134":"1134","1255":"1255","1208":"1208","1219":"1219","Thurrock, Essex, England":"Thurrock, Essex, England, United Kingdom","of, Thurrock, Essex, England":"Thurrock, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Codnor, Derbyshire, England":"Codnor, Derbyshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Grey","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish: variant of   Gray  .","German: dialect variant of   Grau  .","In some cases also an American shortened and altered form of Ukrainian <b>Grushko</b>: nickname or topographic name derived from a Russian-influenced transliteration of <i>grushka</i> ‘pear, pear tree’."],"variants":[{"name":"Gray","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish (especially Eastern Ulster; of Norman origin): habitational name from Graye in Calvados, France, named from the Gallo-Roman personal name <i>Graec(i)us</i>, meaning ‘Greek’ + the locative suffix <i>-acum</i>. This is probably the chief source of the surname in Britain.","English: nickname for someone with gray hair or a gray beard, from Middle English <i>grey</i> (Old English <i>grǣg</i>, <i>grēg</i>) ‘gray’. In Ireland it has been used as a translation of various Gaelic surnames derived from <i>riabhach</i> ‘brindled, gray’, including <b>Mac Giolla Riabhaigh</b>; see   McGreevy  . In North America, this surname has assimilated names with similar meaning from other languages.","French: habitational name from Gray in Haute-Saône or Le Gray in Seine-Maritime."]},{"name":"Greiwe","meanings":["German: possibly a nickname from Middle High German <i>greibe</i> ‘sharp, tangy, dour’. Compare   Grey  ."]}]},{"name":"Hawise","type":"FIRST","meanings":["This female name (which has been corrupted down to Avice and Avis) is from Hadewisa, formed from the German name Hedvig, same as Edwig, which Wachter translates 'propugnator felicitatis;' say, 'fortunate soldier.'"],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hawise De Grey was born about 1162, in England, United Kingdom, her father, de Grey, was 30 and her mother, Mrs de Grey, was 26. She had at least 2 sons with Baron Henry de Grey - Baron Grey of Codnor. She died after 9 March 1240."},"et":{"Abt 1162–after 9 March 1240":"umbes 1162–pärast 9. märtsi 1240","1160–1214":"1160–1214","1162–1240":"1162–1240","1176–1219":"1176–1219","1185–1245":"1185–1245","1208–1255":"1208–1255","1134–Male":"1134–Surnud","1138–Female":"1138–Surnud","after 9 March 1240":"pärast 9. märtsi 1240","1176":"1176","1185":"1185","1240":"1240","1162":"1162","Abt 1208":"umbes 1208","1160":"1160","8 September 1219":"8. september 1219","Abt 1185":"umbes 1185","Abt 1162":"umbes 1162","1138":"1138","1214":"1214","1245":"1245","1134":"1134","1255":"1255","1208":"1208","1219":"1219","Thurrock, Essex, England":"Thurrock, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of, Thurrock, Essex, England":"Thurrock, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Codnor, Derbyshire, England":"Codnor, Derbyshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1162–after 9 March 1240":"noin 1162–9. maaliskuuta 1240 jälkeen","1160–1214":"1160–1214","1162–1240":"1162–1240","1176–1219":"1176–1219","1185–1245":"1185–